Drop sample images here for the load test (`npm run load-test`).

The load test reads everything in this folder that ends in `.jpg`, `.jpeg`,
`.png`, `.heic`, or `.heif`. It uploads each one through the full pipeline
and reports throughput + latency.

Quick way to populate this folder with AI-generated faces (no API key needed):

  for i in $(seq 1 15); do
    curl -s -L -o "fixtures/face-$(printf '%02d' $i).jpg" \
      https://thispersondoesnotexist.com/ -A "Mozilla/5.0"
    sleep 1
  done

Any photos work — your own, Unsplash, etc. A mix of sizes (~500 KB to ~2 MB)
and one HEIC gives the most realistic picture of pipeline throughput.
